sections.Trivia:
- The books Conan buys at the used book store are named after actual detective mangas: "Police in a Box" after Police in a Pod, "The Pharmaceutical Diaries" after The Apothecary Diaries and "Don't Call it a Mistake" after Don't Call it a Mystery.
- The hotel humidifier is a Sharp KC850U.
- While leaving the room, Rinzaki's mistress states that she is an editor from Chūgakukan (中学館), a reference to Daigakukan Publishing (大学館), a well established publishing company in the series, that is in fact named after the publisher of Detective Conan, Shogakukan (小学館).
- The suspects are named after types of black tea[1]:
Danji Rinzaki (林崎 団司) is named after Darjeeling tea ;
Seiko Ronda (論田 盛子) is named after Ceylon tea ;
Aruto Kureishi (暮石 有斗) is named after Earl Grey tea.
